data.title: TechCreate Group Ltd. closed sale of 382,500 shares worth US$0.0002 each to underwriters, gaining more proceeds.
data.description: TechCreate Group Ltd. (NYSE American: TCGL), a technology consultancy and advanced software solutions provider focusing on payment solutions, cybersecurity, and digital services, revealed the completion of an offering of 382,500 class A ordinary shares, valued at US$0.0002 per share. This offering was finalized following the underwriters' full exercise of their over-allotment option. The Company has obtained supplementary gross proceeds from this transaction.

data.title: Columbia Banking System CFO Ronald Farnsworth to step down, Ivan Seda appointed new CFO effective Dec 31, 2025. Nasdaq: COLB.
data.description: The Executive Vice President and CFO, Ronald Farnsworth, will resign from Columbia Banking System, Inc. Ivan Seda, currently the Deputy CFO, will take over as the CFO starting from December 31, 2025. The announcement was made by the parent company of Columbia Bank, Columbia Banking System, Inc. This shift in leadership will take place in Tacoma, Washington. Columbia Banking System, Inc. is listed on the Nasdaq as COLB.

data.title: MasTec (NYSE: MTZ) reports strong Q3 2025 results with double-digit growth in revenue and profit, exceeding guidance. CEO Jose Mas pleased with performance.
data.description: In Coral Gables, Florida, MasTec, Inc. (NYSE: MTZ) revealed their financial results for the third quarter of 2025 along with revised full-year 2025 financial projections. The company reported robust double-digit growth in revenue and profits compared to the previous year, surpassing expectations in all areas. This positive performance was attributed to a significant increase in customer demand across all sectors served by MasTec. Jose Mas, the Chief Executive Officer of MasTec, expressed satisfaction with the quarterly results.

data.title: Netflix to undergo 10-for-1 stock split approved by Board of Directors, impacting NFLX on Nasdaq.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, in Los Gatos, California, Netflix, Inc. (Nasdaq: NFLX) disclosed a significant decision. The company's Board of Directors has given the green light to a ten-for-one forward stock split of its common stock. This means that existing shareholders will receive ten shares for each share they currently own. The split will be executed through a modification to the Company's Amended and Restated agreement. This move is likely to affect the company's stock price and market capitalization, potentially making it more accessible to a broader range of investors.

data.title: Western Digital (Nasdaq: WDC) exceeded revenue and gross margin expectations in Q1 2026, reflecting strong demand environment. CEO Irving Tan pleased with company's performance.
data.description: Western Digital Corp. (Nasdaq: WDC) announced its fiscal Q1 2026 financial results, covering the period ending on October 3, 2025. The company's CEO, Irving Tan, highlighted their success in meeting high demand for data storage in the cloud. Revenue and gross margin figures exceeded the upper limit of projected guidance for the quarter. Tan also emphasized the strong free cash flow generated. The company's performance reflects the impact of AI growth on the industry.

data.title: Atlassian reports Q1 fiscal year 2026 results: Cloud revenue up 26% YoY to $998 million.
data.description: Atlassian Corporation (NASDAQ: TEAM), a prominent provider of team collaboration and productivity software, released financial results for the first quarter ending on September 30, 2025. The company shared a shareholder letter on its website's Investor Relations section. With a strong focus on AI innovation, Atlassian reported significant growth in Cloud revenue for Q1, reaching $998 million, marking a 26% increase compared to the previous year. The company exceeded expectations in this quarter.

data.title: ICF reports 14% revenue increase from commercial and government clients in Q3 2025, with commercial energy clients up 24%.
data.description: In the third quarter, revenues from commercial clients and state & local and international government clients saw a significant increase of 14%, contributing to 57% of total revenues. Specifically, revenues from commercial energy clients surged by 24%. The positive revenue growth was supported by a favorable mix and efficient cost management, leading to margin expansion. Despite the challenging market conditions, the company has managed to maintain its financial outlook.

data.title: Ball Corp (NYSE: BALL) appoints John E. Panichella, CEO of Solenis, to board of directors on 10/30/25. Expert in water treatment and specialty chemicals.
data.description: In Westminster, Colorado on October 30, 2025, Ball Corporation (NYSE: BALL) revealed the addition of John E. Panichella, the CEO of Solenis, to its board of directors. Panichella's expertise in water treatment and specialty chemicals industry enhances the board's composition. His appointment signifies a strategic move by Ball Corporation to leverage Panichella's experience in advancing their business objectives.

data.title: Illumina reports $1.08 billion revenue, flat from Q3 2024. GAAP operating margin 21.0%, non-GAAP 24.5%. EPS: $0.98 (GAAP), $1.34 (non-GAAP).
data.description: In the third quarter of 2025, the company reported a revenue of $1.08 billion, which was unchanged from the same period in 2024 when considering both reported and constant currency basis. The GAAP operating margin for Q3 2025 stood at 21.0%, with the non-GAAP operating margin at 24.5%. Additionally, the GAAP diluted earnings per share (EPS) for the third quarter of 2025 were $0.98, while the non-GAAP diluted EPS was $1.34. The cash provided by the company during this period was not specifically mentioned in the provided text.

data.title: ICF CFO Barry Broadus retiring in 2026 after 40 years; COO James Morgan to become CFO; Anne Choate as President.
data.description: Barry Broadus, a veteran finance professional, will be retiring as Chief Financial Officer in 2026 after dedicating 40 years to the industry. James Morgan, the current Chief Operating Officer, will assume the additional responsibility of CFO following Broadus' retirement. Concurrently, Anne Choate will take on the role of President. This transition is expected to take place on October 30, 2025, as per an official statement from ICF, a prominent global solutions and technology provider traded on the NASDAQ under the ticker symbol ICFI.

data.title: Tosoh Bioscience's GR01 HbA1c Analyzer receives FDA clearance for fast, accurate testing. #diagnostics #healthcare
data.description: A company based in Grove City, Ohio, Tosoh Bioscience, Inc., known for its expertise in clinical diagnostics, has recently obtained clearance from the U.S. FDA for its latest Tosoh Automated Glycohemoglobin Analyzer HLC®-723 GR01 (GR01) for conducting HbA1c tests. This advanced GR01 Analyzer is specifically crafted to enhance the process of HbA1c testing.
